#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1013
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scanner Permissions"
msgstr "扫描仪权限"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1016
msgid ""
"In order to have access to the scanner, a user needs read and write "
"permissions to the device node used by the scanner. In the previous example, "
"the `USB` scanner uses the device node [.filename]#/dev/ugen0.2# which is "
"really a symlink to the real device node [.filename]#/dev/usb/0.2.0#. The "
"symlink and the device node are owned, respectively, by the `wheel` and "
"`operator` groups. While adding the user to these groups will allow access "
"to the scanner, it is considered insecure to add a user to `wheel`. A better "
"solution is to create a group and make the scanner device accessible to "
"members of this group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1018
msgid "This example creates a group called `_usb_`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1022
#, no-wrap
msgid "# pw groupadd usb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1025
msgid ""
"Then, make the [.filename]#/dev/ugen0.2# symlink and the "
"[.filename]#/dev/usb/0.2.0# device node accessible to the `usb` group with "
"write permissions of `0660` or `0664` by adding the following lines to "
"[.filename]#/etc/devfs.rules#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1031
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[system=5]\n"
"add path ugen0.2 mode 0660 group usb\n"
"add path usb/0.2.0 mode 0666 group usb\n"
msgstr ""
"[system=5]\n"
"add path ugen0.2 mode 0660 group usb\n"
"add path usb/0.2.0 mode 0666 group usb\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1036
msgid ""
"It happens the device node changes with the addition or removal of devices, "
"so one may want to give access to all USB devices using this ruleset "
"instead:"
msgstr "设备节点会随着设备的增加或删除而发生变化，因此，人们可能希望使用这个规则集来代替对所有USB设备的访问："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1042
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[system=5]\n"
"add path 'ugen*' mode 0660 group usb\n"
"add path 'usb/*' mode 0666 group usb\n"
msgstr ""
"[system=5]\n"
"add path 'ugen*' mode 0660 group usb\n"
"add path 'usb/*' mode 0666 group usb\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1047
msgid "Refer to man:devfs.rules[5] for more information about this file."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1049
msgid "Next, enable the ruleset in /etc/rc.conf:"
msgstr ""
"另外， 您还需要在 <filename>/etc/rc.conf</filename> 文件中， 启用 "
"<citerefentry><refentrytitle>devfs."
"rules</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> 规则集："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/multimedia/_index.adoc:1053
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
